  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to compare the impact of two non-medicinal strategies: the
      breast-feeding and saccharose to measure effects in cerebral cortex during pain using near
      infrared spectroscopy (NIRS)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Many studies of non-medicinal treatments(saccharose and breast-feeding)show a decrease of
      expression of pain in newborn. However Slater and al questioned these practices due to the
      absence of modification of the cerebral answer measured by evoked potential.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
